category.name: LGBT
description:
This is a social group for gay, lesbian and queer Stockholmers and friends.

We organize events and meetups as a way to meet new people and have fun in this great city. Our activities can range from beer tasting in Söder to camping in the archipelago.

If you're open-minded, culturally curious, enjoy diversity, and want to meet new people while exploring Stockholm, then this group is for you.

If you have suggestions of events, please send a message to one of the organizers (Cando, Magnus Johnsson, and Tim). We love new ideas :)

description:
Stockholm Lesbian Social Club

Looking to meet new friends, join up with old ones, or just get out and have a good time in the heart of Stockholm. This group is for single & couples who wants to meet some new friends. No matter where you from, here on holiday, work or just passing by. Come a long and share your stories. We do all kinds of events from museums, outdoor activities, dancing, have picnics, watch movies, have dinners in and out, clubs and pubs and the list goes on and on. If you want to laugh, hear great stories, have fun and make friends along the way with caring, warm and supportive women then please become a member. Everyone will be included and encouraged to hang out with us. Our goal is simply to meet new women and have a good time! All meetups are picked from your suggestions.

So get creative! What do you want to do?

Mission Statement
The mission statement of the LGBT Alliance is: "Unite individuals in Swedish business who share an interest in LGBT topics in professional life."


Goals

The goals of the LGBT Alliance are to:

• Establish and nurture a peer network for LGBT professionals and our supporters;

• Increase awareness about LGBT business topics;

• Provide a platform for networking; and

• Share best practices and highlight areas for improvement


Member is open to every regardless of employment status, sector of employment (e.g. private, public, NGO, etc), or sexual orientation..

category.name: LGBT
description:
Join Lesbians Who Tech Stockholm and:

> Get geeky with techy folks just like you
> Enjoy tasty adult beverages
> Land gigs, make new friends & connections

Look forward to seeing you all there! :)
---
ABOUT US:

Lesbians Who Tech (LWT) is a community of queer women in tech (and allies) that started in San Francisco in December 2012. Since then, we’ve built a community of over 30,000 queer women in 35 cities, including 5 international cities.

Driving Values of LWT:
> To Be More Visible To Each Other
> To Be More Visible To Others
> To Get More Women And Lesbians In Technology
> To Connect Lesbians Who Tech To LGBTQ And Women’s Organizations Who Are Doing Incredible Work For Community

For more information, please visit: http://lesbianswhotech.org/about/

description:
Quality social events for Lesbian Women were lacking in Stockholm. Well not anymore! This is a group for lesbian who would like to spend some time together, support each other and have fun.

If you feel like to have a nice chat, let's go for a afternoon tea!
If you want to be out of the exhausted world, we go for a hike in forest!
if you have some good idea to have happy time, such as a nice film, museum visiting, let's go for it!

We will try to have weekly event, including fika, walking, hiking, dinner! Bring ideas to make the group as OUR group!

Log off your computer, stash your apps.....it's time to GET SOCIAL!

PS: To be responsible for the group and make girls feel safe being in the group, I need to double check with you that you are truly a lesbian woman.

description:
Quality social events for Lesbian Women were lacking in Stockholm. Well not anymore! This is a group for lesbian who would like to spend some time together, support each other and have fun.

If you want to be out of the exhausted world, we go for a hike in forest!
if you have some good idea to have happy time, such as a nice film, museum visiting, let's go for it!

We will try to have weekly event, including fika, walking, hiking, dinner! Bring ideas to make the group as OUR group!

Log off your computer, stash your apps.....it's time to GET SOCIAL!

description:
Stockholm Lesbian Social Club

Looking to meet new friends, join up with old ones, or just get out and have a good time in the heart of Stockholm. This group is for single & couples who wants to meet some new friends. No matter where you from, here on holiday, work or just passing by. Come a long and share your stories. Everyone will be included and encouraged to hang out with us. Our goal is simply to meet new women and have a good time! All meetups are picked from your suggestions.

So get creative! What do you want to do?

Lesbians Who Tech (LWT) is a community of queer women in tech (and allies) that started in San Francisco in December 2012. Since then, we’ve built a community of over 30,000 queer women in 35 cities, including 5 international cities.

Driving Values of LWT:
> To Be More Visible To Each Other
> To Be More Visible To Others
> To Get More Women And Lesbians In Technology
> To Connect Lesbians Who Tech To LGBTQ And Women’s Organizations Who Are Doing Incredible Work For Community

For more information, please visit: http://lesbianswhotech.org/about/

description:
Quality social events for Lesbian Women were lacking in Stockholm. Well not anymore! This is a group for lesbian who would like to spend some time together, support each other and have fun.

If you feel like to have a nice chat, let's go for a afternoon tea!
If you want to be out of the exhausted world, we go for a hike in forest!
if you have some good idea to have happy time, such as a nice film, museum visiting, let's go for it!

We will try to have weekly event, including fika, walking, hiking, dinner! Bring ideas to make the group as OUR group!

Log off your computer, stash your apps.....it's time to GET SOCIAL!

PS: To be responsible for the group and make girls feel safe being in the group, I need to double check with you that you are truly a lesbian woman.

description:
This is a social group for gay, lesbian and queer Stockholmers and friends.

We organize events and meetups as a way to meet new people and have fun in this great city. Our activities can range from beer tasting in Söder to camping in the archipelago.

If you're open-minded, culturally curious, enjoy diversity, and want to meet new people while exploring Stockholm, then this group is for you.

If you have suggestions of events, please send a message to one of the organizers (Cando, Magnus Johnsson, and Tim). We love new ideas :)

description:
Stockholm Lesbian Social Club

Looking to meet new friends, join up with old ones, or just get out and have a good time in the heart of Stockholm. This group is for single & couples who wants to meet some new friends. No matter where you from, here on holiday, work or just passing by. Come a long and share your stories. We do all kinds of events from museums, outdoor activities, dancing, have picnics, watch movies, have dinners in and out, clubs and pubs and the list goes on and on. If you want to laugh, hear great stories, have fun and make friends along the way with caring, warm and supportive women then please become a member. Everyone will be included and encouraged to hang out with us. Our goal is simply to meet new women and have a good time! All meetups are picked from your suggestions.

So get creative! What do you want to do?

description:
Mission Statement
The mission statement of the LGBT Alliance is: "Unite individuals in Swedish business who share an interest in LGBT topics in professional life."


Goals

The goals of the LGBT Alliance are to:

• Establish and nurture a peer network for LGBT professionals and our supporters;

• Increase awareness about LGBT business topics;

• Provide a platform for networking; and

• Share best practices and highlight areas for improvement


Member is open to every regardless of employment status, sector of employment (e.g. private, public, NGO, etc), or sexual orientation..

description:
Stockholm Lesbian Social Club

Looking to meet new friends, join up with old ones, or just get out and have a good time in the heart of Stockholm. This group is for single & couples who wants to meet some new friends. So get creative! What do you want to do?

The mission statement of the LGBT Alliance is: "Unite individuals in Swedish business who share an interest in LGBT topics in professional life."


Goals

The goals of the LGBT Alliance are to:

• Establish and nurture a peer network for LGBT professionals and our supporters;

• Increase awareness about LGBT business topics;

• Provide a platform for networking; and

• Share best practices and highlight areas for improvement


Member is open to every regardless of employment status, sector of employment (e.g. private, public, NGO, etc), or sexual orientation..

ABOUT US:

Lesbians Who Tech (LWT) is a community of queer women in tech (and allies) that started in San Francisco in December 2012. Since then, we’ve built a community of over 30,000 queer women in 35 cities, including 5 international cities.

Driving Values of LWT:
> To Be More Visible To Each Other
> To Be More Visible To Others
> To Get More Women And Lesbians In Technology
> To Connect Lesbians Who Tech To LGBTQ And Women’s Organizations Who Are Doing Incredible Work For Community

For more information, please visit: http://lesbianswhotech.org/about/

category.name: LGBT
description:
Quality social events for Lesbian Women were lacking in Stockholm. Well not anymore! This is a group for lesbian who would like to spend some time together, support each other and have fun.

If you feel like to have a nice chat, let's go for a afternoon tea!
If you want to be out of the exhausted world, we go for a hike in forest!
if you have some good idea to have happy time, such as a nice film, museum visiting, let's go for it!

We will try to have weekly event, including fika, walking, hiking, dinner! Bring ideas to make the group as OUR group!

Log off your computer, stash your apps.....it's time to GET SOCIAL!

PS: To be responsible for the group and make girls feel safe being in the group, I need to double check with you that you are truly a lesbian woman.
name: Weekly Lesbian Social Stockholm

category.name: LGBT
description:
Quality social events for Lesbian Women were lacking in Stockholm. Well not anymore! This is a group for lesbian who would like to spend some time together, support each other and have fun.

If you feel like to have a nice chat, let's go for a afternoon tea!
If you want to be out of the exhausted world, we go for a hike in forest!
if you have some good idea to have happy time, such as a nice film, museum visiting, let's go for it!

We will try to have weekly event, including fika, walking, hiking, dinner! Bring ideas to make the group as OUR group!

Log off your computer, stash your apps.....it's time to GET SOCIAL!

PS: To be responsible for the group and make girls feel safe being in the group, I need to double check with you that you are truly a lesbian woman.

description:
This is a social group for gay, lesbian and queer Stockholmers and friends.

We organize events and meetups as a way to meet new people and have fun in this great city. Our activities can range from beer tasting in Söder to camping in the archipelago.

If you're open-minded, culturally curious, enjoy diversity, and want to meet new people while exploring Stockholm, then this group is for you.

If you have suggestions of events, please send a message to one of the organizers (Cando, Magnus Johnsson, and Tim). We love new ideas :)

description:
Stockholm Lesbian Social Club

Looking to meet new friends, join up with old ones, or just get out and have a good time in the heart of Stockholm. This group is for single & couples who wants to meet some new friends. No matter where you from, here on holiday, work or just passing by. Come a long and share your stories. We do all kinds of events from museums, outdoor activities, dancing, have picnics, watch movies, have dinners in and out, clubs and pubs and the list goes on and on. If you want to laugh, hear great stories, have fun and make friends along the way with caring, warm and supportive women then please become a member. Everyone will be included and encouraged to hang out with us. Our goal is simply to meet new women and have a good time! All meetups are picked from your suggestions.

So get creative! What do you want to do?

description:
Mission Statement
The mission statement of the LGBT Alliance is: "Unite individuals in Swedish business who share an interest in LGBT topics in professional life."


Goals

The goals of the LGBT Alliance are to:

• Establish and nurture a peer network for LGBT professionals and our supporters;

• Increase awareness about LGBT business topics;

• Provide a platform for networking; and

• Share best practices and highlight areas for improvement


Member is open to every regardless of employment status, sector of employment (e.g. private, public, NGO, etc), or sexual orientation..

category.name: LGBT
description:
Join Lesbians Who Tech Stockholm and:

> Get geeky with techy folks just like you
> Enjoy tasty adult beverages
> Land gigs, make new friends & connections

Look forward to seeing you all there! :)
---
ABOUT US:

Lesbians Who Tech (LWT) is a community of queer women in tech (and allies) that started in San Francisco in December 2012. Since then, we’ve built a community of over 30,000 queer women in 35 cities, including 5 international cities.

Driving Values of LWT:
> To Be More Visible To Each Other
> To Be More Visible To Others
> To Get More Women And Lesbians In Technology
> To Connect Lesbians Who Tech To LGBTQ And Women’s Organizations Who Are Doing Incredible Work For Community

For more information, please visit: http://lesbianswhotech.org/about/

Join Lesbians Who Tech Stockholm and:

> Get geeky with techy folks just like you
> Enjoy tasty adult beverages
> Land gigs, make new friends & connections

Look forward to seeing you all there! :)
---
ABOUT US:

Lesbians Who Tech (LWT) is a community of queer women in tech (and allies) that started in San Francisco in December 2012. Since then, we’ve built a community of over 30,000 queer women in 35 cities, including 5 international cities.

Driving Values of LWT:
> To Be More Visible To Each Other
> To Be More Visible To Others
> To Get More Women And Lesbians In Technology
> To Connect Lesbians Who Tech To LGBTQ And Women’s Organizations Who Are Doing Incredible Work For Community

For more information, please visit: http://lesbianswhotech.org/about/

description:
This is a social group for gay, lesbian and queer Stockholmers and friends.

We organize events and meetups as a way to meet new people and have fun in this great city. Our activities can range from beer tasting in Söder to camping in the archipelago.

If you're open-minded, culturally curious, enjoy diversity, and want to meet new people while exploring Stockholm, then this group is for you.

If you have suggestions of events, please send a message to one of the organizers (Cando, Magnus Johnsson, and Tim). We love new ideas :)

category.name: LGBT
description:
Stockholm Lesbian Social Club

Looking to meet new friends, join up with old ones, or just get out and have a good time in the heart of Stockholm. This group is for single & couples who wants to meet some new friends. No matter where you from, here on holiday, work or just passing by. Come a long and share your stories. We do all kinds of events from museums, outdoor activities, dancing, have picnics, watch movies, have dinners in and out, clubs and pubs and the list goes on and on. If you want to laugh, hear great stories, have fun and make friends along the way with caring, warm and supportive women then please become a member. Everyone will be included and encouraged to hang out with us. Our goal is simply to meet new women and have a good time! All meetups are picked from your suggestions.

So get creative! What do you want to do?

description:
Mission Statement
The mission statement of the LGBT Alliance is: "Unite individuals in Swedish business who share an interest in LGBT topics in professional life."


Goals

The goals of the LGBT Alliance are to:

• Establish and nurture a peer network for LGBT professionals and our supporters;

• Increase awareness about LGBT business topics;

• Provide a platform for networking; and

• Share best practices and highlight areas for improvement


Member is open to every regardless of employment status, sector of employment (e.g. private, public, NGO, etc), or sexual orientation..

category.name: LGBT
description:
Join Lesbians Who Tech Stockholm and:

> Get geeky with techy folks just like you
> Enjoy tasty adult beverages
> Land gigs, make new friends & connections

Look forward to seeing you all there! :)
---
ABOUT US:

Lesbians Who Tech (LWT) is a community of queer women in tech (and allies) that started in San Francisco in December 2012. Since then, we’ve built a community of over 30,000 queer women in 35 cities, including 5 international cities.

Driving Values of LWT:
> To Be More Visible To Each Other
> To Be More Visible To Others
> To Get More Women And Lesbians In Technology
> To Connect Lesbians Who Tech To LGBTQ And Women’s Organizations Who Are Doing Incredible Work For Community

For more information, please visit: http://lesbianswhotech.org/about/

category.name: LGBT
description:
Quality social events for Lesbian Women were lacking in Stockholm. Well not anymore! This is a group for lesbian who would like to spend some time together, support each other and have fun.

If you feel like to have a nice chat, let's go for a afternoon tea!
If you want to be out of the exhausted world, we go for a hike in forest!
if you have some good idea to have happy time, such as a nice film, museum visiting, let's go for it!

We will try to have weekly event, including fika, walking, hiking, dinner! Bring ideas to make the group as OUR group!

Log off your computer, stash your apps.....it's time to GET SOCIAL!

PS: To be responsible for the group and make girls feel safe being in the group, I need to double check with you that you are truly a lesbian woman.

category.name: LGBT
description: This is a group for LGBTQ persons living in Lund and surrounding areas who would like to get together and socialize in the community. I started this group because there is a need for social connection between like minded individuals to get together and share ideas, experiences and what the city has to offer. I am thinking of events like brunch, movies, AfterWork, exhibits, outings, concerts, etc. Why not share some of the great things Lund has to offer with neighbors and friends.
name: Lund LGBT Social Group Meetup
organizer.name: Thomas Ainsworth Robichaux

category.name: LGBT
description:
Hi, I would like to meet people interested in the project of living together under the Rainbow flag, that means anyone who identifies as LGBTIQ and their allies. Are you looking for a place to stay? or are you looking for roommates? Do you have the project of building a house or purchasing a place and share it with others? Let's meet up!
Peace, Catherine
